Reasoning: The paper deals with capacity bounds and results for a communication scenario involving interference channels and cooperative receivers via conferencing links. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of conferencing links to improve channel capacity, which is relevant to the field of signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the Gaussian interference channel, which is a common model in wireless communication and falls under the category of mobile computing and networking (cs.MM) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
